Improvements from 1.7 to 1.7.2
------------------------------

  1. Sleeping Creatures now stop being animated so you can see that
     they are asleep.

  2. Weird bug with simulacrumming a wizard. I was controlling 2
     different wizards who were not in an alliance with each other. I
     had Double in effect. I double simulacrummed the other wizard. I
     simulacrummed the original and then I simulacrummed the copy. I
     hopped one of the wizards on a unicorn and it just disappeared. It
     wasn't there and it couldn't dismount. Ever. The unicorn was still
     there but not the wizard.

  3. Modified the following creatures to take advantage of the new
     combat system: Cobra is now poisonous, Halfling is now @{i}very@{ui} magic
     resistant, Mind Flayer now really attacks intelligence.

  4. Creature Recovery now handles negative recovery rates (Poison),
     though it won't actually kill you yet.

  5. Fixed description of Justice spell.

  6. Numeric keys show player's creatures in RED1 if they have moved
     and in WHITE if they haven't moved.

  7. Fixed Lich spell description.

  8. Pool is now a regular spell. In my opinion it is hard enough to
     use due to Eagles and things that fly up at it and also because it
     adds the "Repair your forces" play mechanic to the game.



@EndNode

@Node "1_7_2-1_7_3" "History.Guide/1_7_2-1_7_3"
